<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Vendor
	Allowances:
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	The Company receives certain
	allowances from vendors primarily related to purchase discounts and markdown
	and damage allowances. All allowances are reflected in Cost of goods sold as
	earned when the related products are sold.&#160; Cash consideration received from a
	vendor is presumed to be a reduction of the purchase cost of merchandise and is
	reflected as a reduction of inventory.&#160; The Company does not receive
	cooperative advertising allowances.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
</EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	Income
	Taxes:
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	The Company files a consolidated federal income tax return. Income
	taxes are provided based on the asset and liability method of accounting,
	whereby deferred income taxes are provided for temporary differences between
	the financial reporting basis and the tax basis of the Company&#8217;s assets and
	liabilities.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
	Unrecognized tax benefits for uncertain tax positions are established in
	accordance with ASC 740 when, despite the fact that the tax return positions
	are supportable, the Company believes these positions may be challenged and the
	results are uncertain.&#160; The Company adjusts these liabilities in light of
	changing facts and circumstances.&#160; Potential accrued interest and penalties
	related to unrecognized tax benefits within operations are recognized as a
	component of Income before income taxes.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	Store
	Opening Costs:
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	Costs relating to the opening of new stores or the
	relocating or
<BR>
	expanding of existing stores are expensed as incurred.&#160; A portion of
	construction, design, and site selection costs are capitalized to new,
	relocated and remodeled stores.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	Closed
	Store Lease Obligations:
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	At the time stores are closed, provisions are made
	for the rentals
<BR>
	required to be paid over the remaining lease terms on a discounted cash flow
	basis, reduced by any expected sublease rentals.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	Insurance:
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	The Company is self-insured with respect to employee health care, workers&#8217;
	compensation and general liability. The Company&#8217;s self-insurance liabilities
	are based on the total estimated cost of claims filed and estimates of claims
	incurred but not reported, less amounts paid against such claims, and are not
	discounted.&#160; Management reviews current and historical claims data in
	developing its estimates. The Company has stop-loss insurance coverage for
	individual claims in excess of $325,000 for employee healthcare, $350,000 for
	workers&#8217; compensation and $250,000 for general liability.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>

	&nbsp;
</H3>

<P ALIGN=CENTER STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">

<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">

<H3 STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0IN;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AVOID;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:0IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	Fair Value of Financial Instruments:
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	The Company&#8217;s carrying values of
	financial instruments, such as cash and cash equivalents, short-term
	investments, restricted cash and short-term investments, approximate their fair
	values due to their short terms to maturity and/or their variable interest
	rates.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</H3>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Stock
	Based Compensation:
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	The Company records
	compensation expense associated with restricted stock and other forms of equity
	compensation in accordance with ASC 718 -
</FONT>
<I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	Compensation &#8211; Stock Compensation.
</FONT>
</I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&#160;
	Compensation cost associated with stock awards recognized in all years presented
	includes: 1) amortization related to the remaining unvested portion of all
	stock awards based on the grant date fair value and 2) adjustments for the
	effects of actual forfeitures versus initial estimated forfeitures.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<H3 STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0IN;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AVOID;TEXT-INDENT:0IN;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&#160;
</FONT>
</B>
</H3>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	Recently Adopted Accounting Policies
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.25IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;">
	In November 2015, the Financial Accounting Standards Board
	issued new accounting guidance that requires entities to present deferred tax
	assets and deferred tax liabilities, along with any related valuation
	allowance, as noncurrent in a balance sheet. The standard is effective for
	annual and interim periods beginning after December 15, 2016, with early
	adoption permitted. We have early adopted this new guidance prospectively
	beginning with the Consolidated Balance Sheet at January 30, 2016. Prior periods
	were not retrospectively adjusted.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.25IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	Recent Accounting Pronouncements
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.25IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;">
	In November 2015, the Financial Accounting Standards Board
	issued an effective date for a new leasing standard that will require
	substantially all leases to be recorded on the balance sheet. The standard is
	effective for the Company&#8217;s first quarter of its 2019 fiscal year; early
	adoption is permitted as of the beginning of an interim or annual reporting
	period. The Company is assessing what impacts this new standard will have on
	its Consolidated Financial Statements.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.25IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.25IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	In May 2014, the
	Financial Accounting Standards Board issued an accounting standards update that
	will supersede most current revenue recognition guidance and modify the
	accounting treatment for certain costs associated with revenue generation.&#160;
</FONT>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	The core principle of the revised revenue
	recognition standard is that an entity should recognize revenue to depict the
	transfer of goods or services to customers in an amount that reflects the
	consideration to which the entity expects to be entitled in exchange for those
	good or services, and provides several steps to apply to achieve that
	principle.&#160; In addition, the new guidance enhances disclosure requirements to
	include more information about specific revenue contracts entered into by the
	entity.&#160; The standard is effective for the Company&#8217;s first quarter of its 2018
	fiscal year, and early adoption is permitted.&#160; The Company is assessing what
	impacts this new standard will have on its Consolidated Financial Statements.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; At January
	30, 2016, the Company&#8217;s investment portfolio was primarily invested in
	governmental debt securities held in managed accounts.&#160; These securities are
	classified as available-for-sale as they are highly liquid and are recorded on
	the Consolidated Balance Sheets at estimated fair value, with unrealized gains
	and temporary losses reported net of taxes in Accumulated other comprehensive
	income.
</FONT>
</FONT>

<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	Company&#8217;s investment portfolio was primarily invested in corporate bonds and tax-exempt
	and taxable governmental debt securities held in managed accounts with
	underlying ratings of A or better at January 30, 2016. The state, municipal and
	corporate bonds and asset-backed securities have contractual maturities which
	range from two days to 5.6 years. The U.S. Treasury Notes and Certificates of
	Deposit have contractual maturities which range from eight months to 1.1 years.
</FONT>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;LETTER-SPACING:-.15PT;">
	These
	securities are classified as available-for-sale and are recorded as Short-term
	investments, Restricted cash and investments and Other assets on the
	accompanying Consolidated Balance Sheets. These assets are carried at fair
	value with unrealized gains and losses reported net of taxes in Accumulated other
	comprehensive income.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">

	&nbsp;

<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
	Additionally, at January 30, 2016, the Company had $0.6 million of corporate
	equities, which are recorded within Other assets in the Consolidated Balance
	Sheets.&#160; At January 31, 2015, the Company had
</FONT>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	$0.3
	million of privately managed funds and $0.6 million of corporate equities, all
	of which are recorded within Other assets in the Consolidated Balance Sheets.&#160;
</FONT>

<DIV>
<P ALIGN=CENTER STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT STYLE="">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	THE
	CATO CORPORATION
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT STYLE="">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	NOTES
	TO CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS&nbsp;&#8212;&nbsp;(Continued)
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;LETTER-SPACING:-.15PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Level 1
	category securities are measured at fair value using quoted active market prices.&#160;
	Level 2 investment securities include corporate and municipal bonds for which
	quoted prices may not be available on active exchanges for identical
	instruments.&#160; Their fair value is principally based on market values determined
	by management with assistance of a third-party pricing service.&#160; Since quoted
	prices in active markets for identical assets are not available, these prices
	are determined by the pricing service using observable market information such
	as quotes from less active markets and/or quoted prices of securities with
	similar characteristics, among other factors.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.25IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	Deferred compensation plan assets consist
	of life insurance policies. These life insurance policies are valued based on
	the cash surrender value of the insurance contract, which is determined based
	on such factors as the fair value of the underlying assets and discounted cash
	flow and are therefore classified within Level 3 of the valuation hierarchy.
	The Level 3 liability associated with the life insurance policies represents a
	deferred compensation obligation, the value of which is tracked via underlying
	insurance funds. These funds are designed to mirror existing mutual funds and
	money market funds that are observable and actively traded. Cash surrender
	values are provided by third parties and reviewed for reasonableness by the
	Company.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">

	years ended

	charges against the allowance for doubtful accounts were approximately $873,000,
	$875,000 and $1,009,000 for the fiscal years ended January 30, 2016, January
	31, 2015 and February 1, 2014, respectively. Expenses relating to the allowance
	for doubtful accounts are classified as a component of Selling, general and
	administrative expense in the accompanying Consolidated Statements of Income
	and Comprehensive Income.

<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	8.&#160;&#160;&#160; Financing Arrangements
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.25IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;LETTER-SPACING:-.15PT;">
	As of January 30,
	2016, the Company had an unsecured revolving credit agreement to borrow $35.0
	million less the balance of revocable credits discussed below.&#160; The revolving
	credit agreement is committed until August 2018.&#160; The credit agreement contains
	various financial covenants and limitations, including the maintenance of
	specific financial ratios with which the Company was in compliance as of
	January 30, 2016.&#160; There were no borrowings outstanding under this credit
	facility during the periods ended January 30, 2016, January 31, 2015 or
	February 1, 2014.&#160; The weighted average interest rate under the credit facility
	was zero at January 30, 2016 due to no borrowings during the year.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;LETTER-SPACING:-.15PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.25IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;LETTER-SPACING:-.15PT;">
	At January 30, 2016
	and January 31, 2015, the Company had no outstanding revocable letters of
	credit relating to purchase commitments. At February 1, 2014, the Company had
	approximately $0.4 million of outstanding revocable letters of credit relating
	to purchase commitments.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	9.&nbsp;&nbsp;Stockholders&#8217; Equity:
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
	The holders of Class&nbsp;A Common Stock are entitled to one vote per share,
	whereas the holders of Class&nbsp;B Common Stock are entitled to ten votes per
	share. Each share of Class&nbsp;B Common Stock may be converted at any time
	into one share of Class&nbsp;A Common Stock. Subject to the rights of the
	holders of any shares of Preferred Stock that may be outstanding at the time,
	in the event of liquidation, dissolution or winding up of the Company, holders
	of Class&nbsp;A Common Stock are entitled to receive a preferential
</FONT>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	distribution of $1.00 per share of the net assets of the
	Company. Cash dividends on the Class&nbsp;B Common Stock cannot be paid unless
	cash dividends of at least an equal amount are paid on the Class&nbsp;A Common
	Stock.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>

<P ALIGN=CENTER STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT STYLE="">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	THE
	CATO CORPORATION
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT STYLE="">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	NOTES
	TO CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS&nbsp;&#8212;&nbsp;(Continued)
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The
	Company&#8217;s certificate of incorporation provides that shares of Class&nbsp;B
	Common Stock may be transferred only to certain &#8220;Permitted Transferees&#8221;
	consisting generally of the lineal descendants of holders of Class&nbsp;B
	Stock, trusts for their benefit, corporations and partnerships controlled by them
	and the Company&#8217;s employee benefit plans. Any transfer of Class&nbsp;B Common
	Stock in violation of these restrictions, including a transfer to the Company,
	results in the automatic conversion of the transferred shares of Class&nbsp;B
	Common Stock held by the transferee into an equal number of shares of
	Class&nbsp;A Common Stock.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
	On March 23, 2016, the Company paid a quarterly dividend of $0.30 per share.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	10.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Employee
	Benefit Plans:
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
	The Company has a defined contribution retirement savings plan (&#8220;401(k) plan&#8221;)
	which covers all associates who meet minimum age and service requirements. The
	401(k) plan allows participants to contribute up to 60% of their annual
	compensation up to the maximum elective deferral, designated by the IRS. The
	Company is obligated to make a minimum contribution to cover plan
	administrative expenses. Further Company contributions are at the discretion of
	the Board of Directors. The Company&#8217;s contributions for the years ended January
	30, 2016, January 31, 2015 and February 1, 2014 were approximately $1,238,000, $1,268,000
	and $1,196,000, respectively.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The Company has a trusteed,
	non-contributory Employee Stock Ownership Plan (&#8220;ESOP&#8221;), which covers
	substantially all associates who meet minimum age and service requirements.&#160;
	The amount of the Company&#8217;s discretionary contribution to the ESOP is
	determined annually by the Compensation Committee of the Board of Directors and
	can be made in Company Class A Common stock or cash.&#160; The Company has chosen to
	contribute cash and the plan purchases stock on the open market consistent with
	prior years.&#160; The Committee approved a contribution of approximately $1,100,000
	for the year ended January 30, 2016. The Company&#8217;s contribution for the year
	ended January 31, 2015 was $7,784,000 and year ended February 1, 2014 was
	$887,000.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The Company is primarily
	self-insured for healthcare.&#160; These costs are significant primarily due to the
	large number of the Company&#8217;s retail locations and associates. The Company&#8217;s
	self-insurance liabilities are based on the total estimated costs of claims
	filed and estimates of claims incurred but not reported, less amounts paid
	against such claims.&#160; Management reviews current and historical claims data in
	developing its estimates. If the underlying facts and circumstances of the
	claims change or the historical trend is not indicative of future trends, then
	the Company may be required to record additional expense or a reduction to
	expense which could be material to the Company&#8217;s reported financial condition
	and results of operations. The Company funds healthcare contributions to a
	third-party provider.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	11.&nbsp;&nbsp;Leases:
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	Company has operating lease arrangements for store facilities and equipment.
	Facility leases generally are at a fixed rate for periods of five years with
	renewal options. For leases with landlord capital improvement funding, the
	funded amount is recorded as a deferred liability and amortized over the term
	of the lease as a reduction to rent expense on the Consolidated Statements of
	Income and Comprehensive Income.&#160; Equipment leases are generally for one to
	three year periods.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>

</A>
<DIV>

<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	12.&nbsp;&nbsp;Income Taxes:
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:9.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; As a
	result of the prospective adoption of the new accounting guidance described in
	Note 1 to the Consolidated Financial Statements, there were no current deferred
	tax assets at January 30, 2016. Current deferred tax assets were $4.3 million
	at January 31, 2015.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Unrecognized
	tax benefits for uncertain tax positions are established in accordance with ASC
	740 when, despite the fact that the tax return positions are supportable, the
	Company believes these positions may be challenged and the results are
	uncertain.&#160; The Company adjusts these liabilities in light of changing facts
	and circumstances.&#160; As of January 30, 2016, the Company had gross unrecognized
	tax benefits totaling approximately $9.6 million, of which approximately $9.8
	million (inclusive of interest) would affect the effective tax rate if
	recognized. The Company had approximately $4.3 million, $4.8 million and $5.4
	million of interest and penalties accrued related to uncertain tax positions as
	of January 30, 2016, January 31, 2015 and February 1, 2014, respectively.&#160; The
	Company recognizes interest and penalties related to the resolution of
	uncertain tax positions as a component of income tax expense.&#160; The Company
	recognized $891,000, $740,000 and $927,000 of interest and penalties in the
	Consolidated Statements of Income and Comprehensive Income for the years ended
	January 30, 2016, January 31, 2015 and February 1, 2014, respectively.&#160; The
	Company is no longer subject to U.S. federal income tax examinations for years
	before 2012.&#160; In state and local tax jurisdictions, the Company has limited
	exposure before 2004.&#160; During the next 12 months, various state and local
	taxing authorities&#8217; statutes of limitations will expire and certain state
	examinations may close, which could result in a potential reduction of
	unrecognized tax benefits for which a range cannot be determined.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;

</FONT>

<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	14.&#160; Reportable Segment Information
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;MARGIN-LEFT:.25IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.25IN;">
<FONT COLOR=BLACK FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT COLOR=BLACK FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LETTER-SPACING:-.15PT;">
	The Company has determined that
	it has four operating segments, as defined under ASC 280-10, including Cato,
	It&#8217;s Fashion, Versona and Credit.&nbsp; As outlined in ASC 280-10, the Company
	has two reportable segments: Retail and Credit.&nbsp; The Company has
	aggregated its three retail operating segments, including e-commerce, based on
	the aggregation criteria outlined in ASC 280-10, which states that two or more
	operating segments may be aggregated into a single reportable segment if aggregation
	is consistent with the objective and basic principles of ASC 280-10, which
	require the segments have similar economic characteristics, products,
	production processes, clients and methods of distribution.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT COLOR=BLACK FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT COLOR=BLACK FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LETTER-SPACING:-.15PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.25IN;">
<FONT COLOR=BLACK FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT COLOR=BLACK FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LETTER-SPACING:-.15PT;">
	The Company&#8217;s retail operating
	segments have similar economic characteristics and similar operating, financial
	and competitive risks.&nbsp; They are similar in terms of product offered, as
	they all offer women&#8217;s apparel, shoes and accessories.&nbsp; Merchandise
	inventory of the Company&#8217;s retail operating segments is sourced from the same
	countries and some of the same vendors, using similar production
	processes.&nbsp; Merchandise for the Company&#8217;s retail operating segments is
	distributed to retail stores in a similar manner through the Company&#8217;s single distribution
	center and is subsequently distributed to clients in a similar manner.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT COLOR=BLACK FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT COLOR=BLACK FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LETTER-SPACING:-.15PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
	&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.25IN;">
<FONT COLOR=BLACK FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT COLOR=BLACK FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LETTER-SPACING:-.15PT;">
	The Company operates its women&#8217;s
	fashion specialty retail stores in 32 states as of
</FONT>
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LETTER-SPACING:-.15PT;">
	January 30, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT COLOR=BLACK FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LETTER-SPACING:-.15PT;">
	, principally in
	the southeastern United States. The Company offers its own credit card to its
	customers and all credit authorizations, payment processing, and collection
	efforts are performed by a separate subsidiary of the Company.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; As of January 30,
	2016, the Company had three long-term compensation plans pursuant to which
	stock-based compensation was outstanding or could be granted. The Company&#8217;s
	1987 Non-Qualified Stock Option Plan is for the granting of options to officers
	and key employees. The 2013 Incentive Compensation Plan and 2004 Incentive
	Compensation Plan are for the granting of various forms of equity-based awards,
	including restricted stock and stock options for grant, to officers, directors
	and key employees. Effective May 23, 2013, shares for grant were no longer
	available under the 2004 Amended and Restated Incentive Compensation Plan.
</FONT>
</FONT>

<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
	In accordance with ASC 718, the fair value of current restricted stock awards
	is estimated on the date of grant based on the market price of the Company&#8217;s
	stock and is amortized to compensation expense on a straight-line basis over a
	five-year vesting period. As of January 30, 2016, there was $12,214,000 of
	total unrecognized compensation expense related to unvested restricted stock
	awards, which is expected to be recognized over a remaining weighted-average vesting
	period of 2.6 years.&#160; The total fair value of the shares recognized as
	compensation expense during the twelve months ended January 30, 2016, January
	31, 2015 and February 1, 2014 was $4,020,000, $3,474,000 and $2,924,000,
	respectively.&#160; The expenses are classified as a component of Selling, general
	and administrative expenses in the Consolidated Statements of Income and
	Comprehensive Income.
</FONT>
</FONT>

<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	The Company&#8217;s Employee Stock Purchase Plan allows eligible
	full-time employees to purchase a limited number of shares of the Company&#8217;s
	Class A Common Stock during each semi-annual offering period at a 15% discount
	through payroll deductions. During the twelve month period ended January 30,
	2016, the Company sold&#160; 16,305 shares to employees at an average discount of
	$5.29 per share under the Employee Stock Purchase Plan. The compensation
	expense recognized for the 15% discount given under the Employee Stock Purchase
	Plan was approximately $86,000, $90,000 and $70,000 for fiscal years 2015, 2014
	and 2013, respectively.&#160; These expenses are classified as a component of
	Selling, general and administrative expenses.&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	The stock option expense was $17,000,
	$17,000 and $13,000 for the twelve months ended January 30, 2016, January 31,
	2015 and February 1, 2014, respectively.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">

	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Stock option awards outstanding
	under the Company&#8217;s current plans were granted at exercise prices which were
	equal to the market value of the Company&#8217;s stock on the date of grant, vest
	over five years, and expire no later than ten years after the grant date.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">

<EFX_CONTROL_AND_PROCEDURES>
<A NAME="FIS_CONTROL_AND_PROCEDURES"></A>
<DIV ALIGN=LEFT>
<TABLE CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0 BORDER=0 STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE;WIDTH:539.900024PT;">
<TR>
<TD VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=9% STYLE="PADDING:0IN 0IN 0IN 0IN;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	Item&nbsp;9A.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=91% STYLE="PADDING:0IN 0IN 0IN 0IN;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<B>
<I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	Controls and Procedures:
</FONT>
</I>
</B>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:9.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0IN;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AVOID;TEXT-INDENT:0IN;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	Conclusion Regarding the
	Effectiveness of Disclosure Controls and Procedures
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:9.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;We carried out an evaluation,
	with the participation of our Principal Executive Officer and Principal
	Financial Officer, of the effectiveness of our disclosure controls and
	procedures as of January 30, 2016.&#160; Based on this evaluation, our Principal
	Executive Officer and Principal Financial Officer concluded that, as of January
	30, 2016, our disclosure controls and procedures, as defined in Rule 13a-15(e),
	under the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 (the &#8220;Exchange Act&#8221;), were effective
	to ensure that information we are required to disclose in the reports that we
	file or submit under the Exchange Act is recorded, processed, summarized and
	reported within the time periods specified in the SEC&#8217;s rules and forms and
	that such information is accumulated and communicated to our management,
	including our Principal Executive Officer and Principal Financial Officer, as
	appropriate to allow timely decisions regarding required disclosure.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:9.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0IN;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AVOID;TEXT-INDENT:0IN;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	Management&#8217;s Report on Internal
	Control Over Financial Reporting
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0IN;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AVOID;TEXT-INDENT:0IN;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:9.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Management
	is responsible for establishing and maintaining adequate internal control over
	financial reporting, as defined in Exchange Act Rule 13a-15(f).&#160; Under the
	supervision and with the participation of our management, including our
	Principal Executive Officer and Principal Financial Officer, we carried out an
	evaluation of the effectiveness of our internal control over financial reporting
	as of January 30, 2016 based on the
</FONT>
<I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;">
	Internal Control &#8211; Integrated Framework
</FONT>
</I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;">
</FONT>
<I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;">
	(2013)
</FONT>
</I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;">
	issued by the Committee of Sponsoring Organizations of the
	Treadway Commission (&#8220;COSO&#8221;).&#160; Based on this evaluation, management concluded
	that our internal control over financial reporting was effective as of January
	30, 2016.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:9.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;PricewaterhouseCoopers
	LLP, our independent registered public accounting firm, has audited the
	effectiveness of our internal control over financial reporting as of January
	30, 2016, as stated in its report which is included herein.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:9.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0IN;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AVOID;TEXT-INDENT:0IN;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	Changes in Internal Control Over
	Financial Reporting
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:9.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;No
	change in the Company&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting (as defined
	in Exchange Act Rule 13a-15(f)) has occurred during the Company&#8217;s fiscal quarter
	ended January 30, 2016 that has materially affected, or is reasonably likely to
	materially affect, the Company&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting.
</FONT>
</P>
</EFX_CONTROL_AND_PROCEDURES>

<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:7.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">

<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	the Annual Report on

	Securities Exchange Act of 1934; and
